Company Description


For more than 20 years, KordaMentha has supported businesses through some of their most complex matters and opportunities. Founder owned and led; we are an advisory firm that helps corporations, financiers, lawyers, private investors and government clients to grow, protect and recover value.

That’s what we do, but it’s how we do this that makes us who we are.

Proudly independent, strategically local, and with a bias for action to get things done, we focus on doing what is right by our clients, our people, and the wider community. Our track record shows that we help navigate the best path forward in challenging times, and do so across cities, regions and territories.

In the most stressful or demanding environments, we continue to drive change where it really counts.

Job Description


Our Performance Improvement team is growing rapidly and is looking for a motivated Associate Director. As an Associate Director you will partner with clients on a diverse range of engagements from strategic reviews through to delivery of operational and financial performance improvement solutions. Specifically, you will:

collaborate with our team and clients to develop and deliver impactful engagements across a range of industries 
analyse financial information, identify issues and prepare recommendations for our clients 
assist clients to evaluate and understand the performance and position of their business; and
proactively create and implement solutions that are as varied as the challenges our clients face. 

This role works alongside Partners, with constant connections with clients and across the firm. You will enjoy:

Genuine exposure to senior leaders – you will provide support to the senior team members and will be relied on as a meaningful contributor.
Market leading engagements – we are brought in for complex engagements when significant value is at risk, whether it is financial, reputational or otherwise. Our clients are often at the most difficult crossroad in their history, and this makes the work important, interesting, and educational.
Meaningful work – our engagements are highly commercial, with an emphasis on developing impactful solutions to improve the bottom line and operations. As a team, our bias is towards rapid decision making and is grounded in deep analysis and learnings from client interactions.  

Qualifications


As an ideal candidate for this role, you will have:

Tertiary qualifications combined with 6-8 years’ experience, including experience in professional services.
An intellectually and commercially curious mindset to understand how businesses operate from the inside.
Experience in diagnosing and solving complex commercial issues.
Demonstrating attention to and passion for detail.
Strong financial and operational skills.
Strong analysis, financial modelling and / or report development skills.
Exceptional interpersonal & communication skills to influence stakeholders to successful outcomes.
A willingness to travel interstate as required.

Preferred:

Higher Education experience is preferred

Additional Information


At KordaMentha, we offer far more than just a job—we offer an opportunity to grow your career, expand your professional network, and make a tangible impact. As an integral part of our team, you'll collaborate closely with senior leaders in a firm that thrives on innovation and high-performance culture.

At KordaMentha, we believe there is strength in difference. Our entrepreneurial spirit expands the possibilities for action. We approach situations, challenges, and opportunities with optimism, curiosity, and diversity of thought. We seek novel solutions to problems and encourage unconventional and innovative approaches. 

Our team's diverse skillsets, backgrounds and experiences fuel KordaMentha's different mindset. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply, recognising that talent and potential extend beyond traditional qualifications. Our selection process values diverse perspectives and considers each applicant's unique strengths and capabilities.

Join a high-performing risk analytics team where you will play a key role in monitoring and improving credit risk models that support critical business decisions. This is an excellent opportunity for someone with a quantitative mindset and strong data skills to work in a collaborative, forward-thinking environment.


The role:


You will be responsible for monitoring the performance of credit risk models, identifying issues, and providing insights that drive model improvements and better decision-making. You will work closely with model owners, developers, and risk stakeholders across the business.
Key responsibilities include:

Generating regular model monitoring results across a suite of credit risk models
Developing monitoring processes for newly implemented models
Reviewing monitoring outcomes and highlighting trends or issues
Providing clear, actionable insights to model owners and developers
Participating in monitoring review meetings with senior stakeholders
Presenting results through effective data visualisation
Supporting internal and external data requests
Maintaining and enhancing monitoring approaches and frameworks
Tracking issues through to resolution
Contributing to broader credit risk and modelling transformation projects
Documenting monitoring processes and procedures
Supporting monitoring of PD, LGD, EAD and IFRS9 models

About you

You have a foundational understanding of credit risk modelling within a banking or financial services environment and are comfortable working with data, models, and frameworks.
Your skills and experience include:
Understanding of credit risk frameworks and model lifecycle concepts
Knowledge of statistical modelling data and monitoring requirements
SAS, SQL and Excel capability
Experience with data visualisation tools such as Tableau
Good understanding of data management and system development lifecycle principles
Strong written and verbal communication skills
Ability to work with a range of stakeholders including modellers, data teams, systems teams and offshore partners

What's on offer

Strong career development and learning opportunities
Supportive and collaborative team culture
Flexible working arrangements
Opportunity to contribute to meaningful risk and analytics initiatives

How to apply


If you are interested in applying your analytical skills in a role that combines data, risk and stakeholder engagement, we would love to hear from you. Apply now to be considered.

About the role

Based at our Corporate office in Homebush West, this role is ideal for an experienced SAP Business Intelligence Developer with strong capability in SAP BW and HANA. You will work closely with business stakeholders and technical teams to deliver high‑quality reporting and analytics that support informed decision‑making across the organisation.

You will also:

Provide expertise in SAP BW and HANA build, testing, deployment, and ongoing support.
Engage with business and technical stakeholders to gather requirements, evaluate solution options, and perform impact analysis.
Recommend and implement SAP BW and HANA best practices and development standards.
Collaborate with reporting and business analysts to clarify functional and technical requirements.
Enhance and streamline analytics, reporting, and information management processes.
Contribute to the design and optimisation of HANA data models.
Deliver reliable BAU support for analytics, reporting, and operational needs.
Lead issue resolution activities, ensuring timely investigation and problem‑solving.
Maintain accurate, high‑quality technical documentation for analytics and reporting development.

About you

You are an experienced SAP BW professional with a minimum of five years’ hands-on experience delivering solutions across at least two full end‑to‑end SAP BW lifecycle implementations and production support. You have strong expertise in SAP BW on HANA or BW4HANA and SAP HANA modelling, with proven experience designing and developing Calculation Views and Composite Providers.

You will also have:  

Strong understanding of data warehousing principles, architecture, and design strategies.
Experience with SAP reporting tools such as Web Intelligence, Analysis for Office, and SAP Analytics Cloud (SAC).
Knowledge of SAP enhancement techniques including User Exits, BADIs, and Enhancement Spots.
Integration experience across SAP ECC, SAP S/4 Finance, and non-SAP systems.
Experience developing ABAP CDS Views in SAP S/4.
Exposure to Business Objects Data Services (BODS) and SAP Datasphere.

This opportunity will provide: 

Exposure to a diverse range of organisational stakeholders, initiatives, and projects, enhancing your skillset and competencies.
A supportive and collaborative working environment.
Experience working with an Iconic Australian Brand with global success in Australia, NZ, Asia, and Europe. 
Employee benefits including salary packaging and discounted purchases on a great range of products and services.

Ad Text:
Gold Fields Group Services (Pty) Ltd




Drive portfolio and market insights across a diverse international asset base
Senior level role with generous incentives & flexible work arrangements
Strong financial modelling, market analysis & strategic thinking essential

The Opportunity:

Work closely with a diverse, high‑calibre team to shape the long‑term direction of Gold Fields. In this pivotal role within Corporate Development, you'll make a meaningful impact by delivering clear, insightful analysis that informs group‑wide strategic priorities.

You'll contribute by collaborating across business units to assess market trends, help define and support delivery of our global strategy, contribute to the development of strategic plans for each asset within our portfolio, and deliver strategic initiatives that strengthen the company's global position.

Why You'll Love Working for Us

Permanent role with a leading global gold producer
9‑day fortnight and hybrid working options
As a Leader you'll receive short and long term incentives
5 weeks annual leave, long service leave after 5 years,
Paid parental leave

What You'll Do

Lead the annual strategic planning cycle, including scenario modelling and long‑term portfolio analysis
Deliver portfolio valuation economics and alternative portfolio configurations to inform strategic decisions
Conduct industry, competitive and market analysis across multiple geographies
Translate complex analysis into clear, actionable insights for senior leaders
Partner with global business units to align strategy, assess performance and identify value‑creation opportunities
Prepare strategy papers and presentations for Executive Leadership and Board‑level forums
Monitor sector trends, geopolitical developments and global factors shaping future strategy

What You'll Bring

Significant experience in mining, management consulting, investment banking, business development, or a related strategic/analytical role
Bachelor's degree in finance, business, engineering, economics or a related discipline (advanced qualifications advantageous)
Demonstrated ability to deliver concise, high‑impact analysis for senior stakeholders
Strong financial modelling, market evaluation and strategic thinking capabilities
Experience working across global markets or multiple jurisdictions would be desirable
A growth mindset, with strong communication, accountability, and relationship‑building skills



About Gold Fields

At Gold Fields, we believe great leadership is grounded in empathy, respect, and growth. Join Gold Fields and be part of a company where people, passion, and purpose come together to create enduring value beyond mining.


Join an organisation endorsed by WORK180 for our commitment to creating an environment where inclusion and belonging matter, and you can build meaningful, long-term careers in mining, with fabulous mentors to guide you through from day one.

We recognise that everyone's circumstances are unique. We're always open to conversations about flexible working arrangements that can help you balance work, family, and life.

How to Apply

To work for a company that aligns with your purpose, apply now at https://careers.goldfields.com/Australia

About AARNet


Australia’s Academic and Research Network (AARNet) was established in 1989 and is widely regarded as the founder of the Internet in Australia and renowned as the architect, builder, and operator of world-class network infrastructure for research and education.

As Australia’s National Research and Education Network (NREN). We connect over one million users — researchers, faculty, staff, students, hospitals, vocational training providers, schools, and museums — across Australia.

We are an organisation of innovators, doers, and courageous thinkers. We don’t settle for the status quo; instead, we anticipate the future needs of our customers and build solutions today.

Role Purpose


The Senior Strategy Manager is responsible for developing, driving and monitoring the organisation’s long-term strategic direction. This role partners closely with the executive leadership to identify growth opportunities, and evaluate market trends and ongoing conditions. The Senior Strategy Manager is the conduit that allows strategic vision and priorities to be translated into actionable plans that deliver sustainable and measurable business impact.

This role will support the Director Product & Commercial and be accountable for the operational aspects of the annual strategic planning process. This includes facilitating executive and senior leadership workshops including but not limited to the annual planning and revision sessions, collaborating across the company and externally with subject matter experts, and presenting to the AARNet Audit, Finance and Risk Committee and the AARNet Board as required.

The Senior Strategy Manager is accountable for measuring strategy execution through aligned KPIs and partnering with Executives to monitor progress and mitigation efforts.With proven and relevant experience in the telecommunication sector, the Senior Strategy Manager will be astute to changes in the dynamic landscape and interpret these into potential threats and opportunities for AARNet. They will also be adept in sourcing data and performing high quality analysis. The Senior Strategy Manager will support executive workstream leaders in the strategic evaluation of programs and objectives, ensuring ongoing alignment to the corporate direction of AARNet.

Key Accountabilities


Strategic Planning & Execution

Lead the development of short, and medium-term business strategies aligned with company vision and goals.
Translate strategic objectives into clear and actionable initiatives and roadmaps, with clearly articulated and measurable outcomes.
Monitor the execution of strategic initiatives and collaborate with stakeholders to accelerate progress and ensure timely delivery.

Market & Competitive Analysis

Analyse market trends, customer insights, and competitive dynamics to ensure an ongoing understanding of the threat and opportunity landscape as applicable to AARNet.
Identify growth opportunities, risks, and potential areas for differentiation.
Lead strategic assessments for new markets, products, or business models or ideas.

Business Performance & Insights

Develop frameworks and KPIs to track strategic performance.
Provide data-driven insights and recommendations to executive leadership.
Support annual planning, budgeting, and forecasting processes.

Stakeholder Collaboration

Work cross-functionally with Product, Operations, and Customer Relations, Finance, and People & Culture, to align strategy and execution.
Present strategic recommendations to the executive team and Board.
Expertise, experience & qualifications

Relevant degree in Business, Economics, Finance, or a related field (MBA or equivalent preferred).
10+ years of experience in strategy, management consulting, corporate development, or a related role, preferably in a Telecommunications orTechnology enironment.
Proven experience developing and executing business strategies including market analysis and investment cases.
Knowledge of the Research and Education sector preferred but not essential.
Strong analytical, problem-solving, and critical-thinking skills.
Strong commercial and financial acumen.
Experience working closely with executive leadership and board of directors.
Ability to operate in an ambiguous environment
Advanced communication skills in influencing, presentation and storytelling.
Must have a strategic mindset with a hands-on execution approach.
Conditions of employment

AARNet is committed to diversity and providing equal opportunity to all. We are a great place to work if you want to make a difference. Remuneration will be based on skills and experience and will include an above-market superannuation package.
At AARNet, all employees are responsible for:
 Actively promoting safe work practices in the workplace ensuring all activities are consistent with AARNet’s policies and comply with all WH&S legislation, policies, and procedures;
Actively contributing to a safe and supportive working environment that is inclusive of all staff;
Compliance with all workplace directions and processes;
Compliance with the applicable contract of employment; and
Maintaining a standard of performance that is acceptable to AARNet.

Bring your curiosity. Build your capability. Help shape the cities of tomorrow.

At Mirvac, we're proud of our 54‑year legacy - but we're even more excited about what's next. We reimagine urban life by creating places where people and communities thrive, and we do it by putting people first, acting with integrity and working together.

We're looking for a Capital Transaction Analyst to join our Sydney team, a role that offers meaningful exposure to complex transactions, experienced leaders and a collaborative, high‑performing culture.

Our opportunity

This role sits at the heart of how Mirvac creates long‑term value. You'll support the execution of acquisitions, disposals and strategic capital initiatives across a diversified portfolio of office, retail and industrial assets.

Working closely with senior leaders, you'll apply strong financial and market analysis to support quality, well‑considered investment decisions, contributing to outcomes that leave a lasting legacy for our investors and communities.

This is an ideal opportunity for an Analyst who is curious, commercially minded and motivated by learning through real exposure.

What you'll be doing

Analysing financial and operational performance of assets to support acquisition, disposal and development decisions
Building and reviewing financial models, cashflows and valuations using Excel and Forbury, aligned to Mirvac's return hurdles
Supporting valuation assessments through market research, comparable sales and rental analysis, and future trend insights
Coordinating transaction due diligence, managing data rooms and clearly communicating findings
Assisting with external consultant management, including valuers, agents and legal advisers
Preparing transaction materials, budgets, programs and investment proposals
Supporting Investment Committee and Board approval processes, ensuring strong governance and compliance
Working collaboratively across Asset Management, Development, Legal, Tax, Finance and Research teams
Building relationships with capital partners, agents and industry consultants
Staying abreast of market activity and maintaining accurate transaction data
Contributing to broader strategic initiatives and special projects as required

What you'll bring

Aligned work experience gained in a medium to large organisation within the property industry
Strong financial modelling skills with advanced Excel capability (Forbury experience desirable)
A relevant tertiary qualification in Property, Land Economics, Business or Commerce
A high level of attention to detail and strong organisational skills
A collaborative, team‑oriented mindset with the confidence to engage with stakeholders at all levels
Sound judgement, discretion and professionalism
A proactive, learning‑oriented approach and the ability to juggle competing priorities

Life at Mirvac

At Mirvac, how we work matters. We put people first, support flexible ways of working, invest in development and learning, and foster an inclusive, respectful environment where everyone belongs.

You'll be empowered to grow, supported by experienced leaders and surrounded by people who care about quality, impact and legacy.

All of these attributes are preferred, if you think you may be the right fit for the role please still apply.

Computer Systems Officer Level 5

$176,910 pa. Package includes salary from $149,739 to $156,088, plus employer's contribution to superannuation of 12% and annual leave loading.


About us

The NSW Police Force (NSWPF) is one of the largest police forces in the western world, with more than 20,000 employees, including more than 4,000 administrative employees who support the sworn officers that provide a range of law and order services 24 hours a day, seven days a week to the socially, geographically and culturally diverse community of NSW.


About the role

We have an opportunity for 4 Senior ICT Business Analysts to be part of our Project Management Office (PMO), Technology and Communication Services Command. The Senior ICT Business Analyst works with relevant stakeholders to understand business needs; capture, analyse and document requirements; and support the delivery of ICT solutions that meet business needs.

Join the PMO team at NSW Police Force as a Senior ICT Business Analyst and play a key role in delivering technology solutions that enable critical policing and corporate operations. We are recruiting four senior roles across a diverse portfolio of programs, including critical network and infrastructure, cyber security, and other major enterprise IT initiatives spanning the organisation. 

In this role, you will work closely with business and technical stakeholders to understand complex needs, elicit and analyse requirements, and support the delivery of ICT capabilities that drive strategic, operational, and risk-based outcomes. You will contribute across multiple disciplines and programs, bringing flexibility and depth of experience to environments with high operational impact. 

You will bring demonstrated high-level business analysis expertise, with significant experience delivering end-to-end analysis across complex, multi-stream programs and projects. Your ability to conduct gap and impact analyses, develop business cases, and translate technical and architectural concepts into clear, plain-language artefacts will be critical to optimising performance and enabling continuous improvement. These roles require strong knowledge of enterprise architecture frameworks, ICT governance, and project delivery methodologies. You will support the integration of new and emerging capabilities, particularly within critical infrastructure, cyber security, and core ICT platforms, while ensuring alignment with organisational strategy, standards, and regulatory obligations.

View the relevant role description for more information on this role (e.g. essential requirements, key accountabilities, key challenges and capabilities required for the role)


What we can offer you

At NSWPF our people have access to a range of benefits that help balance life at work and at home. Some of the benefits available when you join the NSWPF include:

competitive salary;
flexible work options;
opportunity to purchase leave;
annual leave loading;
corporate wellbeing programs including seminars and the Fitness Passport;
free annual influenza vaccination;
salary packaging options via superannuation contributions or a novated vehicle lease;
convenient location for public transport and to shops etc; and 
in-house gym facilities. (Parramatta)

How to Apply

Applications can only be submitted electronically via the I Work for NSW website.

To be considered for this role, attach a cover letter (2 pages maximum) and an up-to-date resume that clearly details your skills & experience as relevant to this role.

Please do not attach copies of qualifications, certificates or documentation (other than what has been requested) - you can bring these if called for interview.

Please address each of the following Target Questions (500 words per question) in the text boxes provided in the online application or attach as a separate document.

Target Question 1:

Describe how you delivered end-to-end business analysis on complex ICT projects, including your approach to requirements management, as-is/to-be and gap analysis, alignment with enterprise architecture and governance, the artefacts you produced, please include the ICT streams you worked with.

Target Question 2:

Describe an example where you worked with stakeholders to gather and manage requirements, outlining your role, how the requirements were approved, and how governance supported decisions and alignment.

Your application must stand on its own merits, and the completeness and relevance of your application will determine if you proceed through to the selection process.

If you require any further information about this opportunity, please contact Gemma Cacciola via (02) 8835 8331.

To be eligible to apply for this role, you must meet one of the following statuses: 

an Australian Citizen;
a permanent resident of Australia; or
a New Zealand citizen.

Prior to commencement, the successful candidate will be required to undergo a rigorous National Police (criminal history) Check and obtain and maintain a Security Clearance as determined by the NSW Police Force.

Our commitment to Diversity:

At the NSW Police Force, we are proud to be an employer of a diverse range of people. We are committed to reflecting the diverse community we serve and creating an inclusive and respectful workplace for all employees where differences are embraced, contributions are valued, and everyone has a sense of connection and belonging.

We welcome applications from individuals with diverse skills, experiences, and backgrounds including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, LGBTQIA+ individuals, people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, those from culturally and linguistically diverse communities, and people of all ages.

Job Title: Head of Category and Channel Strategy
Ad Text:
Are You Ready to Make It Happen at Mondelēz International? 
Join our Mission to Lead the Future of Snacking. Make It With Pride. 




Mondelēz International empowers people to snack right in over 150 countries around the world. We're leading the future of snacking with iconic global and local brands such as Oreo, Cadbury, Philadelphia, Pascall, The Natural Confectionery Company, Belvita, Ritz and Toblerone with global revenues exceeding $31 billion USD. 




The Opportunity:

We are seeking an experienced, innovative and curious Head of Category and Channel Strategy to join our team. This pivotal role involves developing and managing a long-term collaborative framework to drive sustainable category growth across diverse customer segments and channels, while also defining organisational roles and aligning priorities effectively with our strategic customers.

This role will serve as the key sales liaison for internal Category Strategy development, ensuring robust customer representation, and will be instrumental in developing "How to Win" customer/channel strategies that empower account teams and customers to achieve long-term growth. 

 

How you will contribute: 

Create and maintain a continuous review of the longer-term (3-5yrs) strategic agenda for customer categories (Confectionery, Biscuits, Seasonal, Soft White, Baking). 

Development of strong working relationships & category captaincy in insights with multiple customer groups. 

Acting as key lead and driver of the Customer JBP and plan on a page development, projects, timelines and initiatives. 

Be the business lead in internal category strategy development to ensure strong customer representation. 

Facilitate and coordinate projects, providing support to project team leads from across the business. 

Leveraging global and local insight / learnings and best practices in shopper missions, occasion-based marketing, and merchandising. 




About you: 

Strong Experience working across category development, customer account management and revenue management. 

Proficiency in data analytics and consumer and shopper insights. 

Strong leadership and the ability to build trust and robust working relationships internally and externally. 




No Relocation support available.




Business Unit Summary

At Mondelez International, our mission is to provide consumers with the right snack, for the right moment, made in the right way. We are one of the largest snack companies in the world, with global net revenues exceeding $31 billion USD.

The Role

What you’ll do

Advanced Microsoft Excel skills including VBA, PowerQuery, PowerPivot. 
High attention to detail and proven ability to deliver quality outcomes.

Ad Text:
Company description:



Insignia Financial Limited is an Australian financial services company which offers a range of products and services including financial advice, superannuation, investment management and trustee services



Job description:



We're seeking an experienced Senior Investment Analyst - Transition Management to play a critical role in managing complex, multi-asset class transitions within a multi-manager trust investment structure across Super and non-Super clients.

This role sits at the intersection of investment strategy, execution, and stakeholder management, partnering closely with MLC Asset Management to ensure asset management changes are implemented efficiently, cost-effectively, and with minimal risk, ultimately delivering better performance outcomes for members and clients.

How You'll Make an Impact

You'll be responsible for the end-to-end planning and execution of investment transitions, ensuring smooth delivery, strong governance, and best execution outcomes in a highly collaborative environment.

Key Responsibilities & Capabilities

Manage end-to-end asset transition projects across multi-asset, Super and non-Super unit trust structures, following approved investment changes
Plan and coordinate complex transitions including manager terminations and appointments, asset movements, legacy asset migration, and internal unit trust registry changes
Propose and implement transition strategies, considering member impact, unit registry transactions, liquidity, market impact, buy/sell spreads, tax (CGT, stamp duty), and implicit/explicit transaction costs
Appoint, coordinate, and monitor external transition managers and custodians, ensuring strong risk management, governance, and execution quality
Act as the central point of coordination across Investment, Fund Accounting & Operations, Custody, Product, and Legal to keep timelines, pipelines, and dependencies on track
Provide trading and execution advice (understanding trade execution and life cycle, without executing trades) and support cost analysis and financial modelling
Support new business activity including RFPs, pitches, and presentations, contributing analytical insight on asset allocation and investment structures
Build strong relationships with senior investment professionals through clear communication, proactive problem-solving, and a solutions-focused mindset

What you'll bring:

Extensive experience in financial services, wealth or asset management, with strong exposure to Unit Trust structures
Proven understanding of asset transition management and investment implementation within complex investment structures
Strong risk management mindset, able to question assumptions and assess downstream impacts
Solid knowledge of asset movements, execution strategies, liquidity, buy/sell spreads, and market impacts
Understanding of portfolio construction, asset allocation, and liquidity management, including tax considerations (e.g. CGT)
Highly organised and able to manage multiple concurrent, project-based transitions
Strong analytical and financial modelling skills, with advanced Excel capability
Autonomous, solutions-focused professional with strong stakeholder management and communication skills

This is a flat-structured team, but with exceptional exposure to senior investment professionals, complex investment decisions, and high-impact projects across the investment function. It's an ideal role for someone who wants breadth, depth, and visibility rather than a narrow operational pathway.

To Apply

Read more about why you should join our team https://www.insigniafinancial.com.au/careers/working-with-us/why-join-our-team.

Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and at a minimum be required to undertake police and basic credit checks as a condition of employment.

Company Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, 你好, hallo, vítejte!
Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be time-consuming, so let’s get straight to the point.

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney, with additional spaces in Melbourne, Brisbane, Perth, and Adelaide. You have the flexibility to work from the office, home, or a mix of both—it’s your choice. We trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.

Job Description


What you’d be doing in this role

As Canva scales, change is part of our DNA. While your role will evolve over time, here’s a flavour of what you’ll be working on when you start:

Leading Product Analytics Engineering: Own and lead the Analytics Engineering function for the Product Org, with Product AEs reporting to you and the team expected to grow over time.

Driving Analytics Architecture of the Future: Define, own, and evolve Canva’s Product Analytics Engineering architecture, including modular data domains, semantic layers, metrics systems, and AI-ready foundations.

Elevating Analytics Engineering (AE) Craft: Set clear standards and best practices for analytics engineering across Product, and coach AEs across levels to consistently deliver high-quality, scalable data assets.

Partnering Across Product & Data: Work closely with Product Managers, Data Scientists, Engineers, and Platform teams to translate complex product needs into robust, reusable analytics solutions.

Balancing Strategy and Delivery: Combine long-term architectural thinking with pragmatic execution, ensuring AE effort is focused on the highest-impact Product initiatives.

Acting as a Technical Leader: Be the senior escalation point for complex analytics problems and represent Analytics Engineering perspectives in Product and Data leadership forums.

Enabling Product Decisions: Ensure analytics foundations enable product discovery, experimentation, launches, and long-term strategy, helping teams confidently understand user behaviour, product performance, and the impact of their decisions.

Hands-on Where It Matters Most: Get actively involved in complex or high-leverage analytics engineering work, while setting the technical direction for the team.

You're probably a match if…

You have extensive experience across Analytics Engineering, Data Engineering, or Software Engineering roles.

You’ve led and coached Analytics Engineering teams, including managing senior engineers and growing teams.

You’re deeply experienced with modern data platforms and tooling (e.g. SQL-based warehouses such as Snowflake, dbt-style transformations, orchestration, and semantic layers).

You have strong opinions (weakly held) — backed by experience — on data modelling, analytics architecture, and platform scalability and are eager to try new approaches.

You’re comfortable operating at the intersection of technical depth, people leadership, and strategy.

You thrive on collaboration and can communicate clearly with both highly technical partners and senior non-technical stakeholders.

You care deeply about data quality, reliability, performance, and cost efficiency.

About the team

Analytics Engineering sits within Canva’s broader Data ecosystem. The Product Analytics Engineering team partners closely with Product, Design and Engineering to ensure Canva’s product decisions are powered by trusted, timely, and scalable data foundations.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard—and we do—but you’ll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity, and fun woven throughout life at Canva. Here’s a taste of what’s on offer:

Equity packages: We want our success to be yours too.

Inclusive parental leave policy: Supporting all parents and carers.

Annual Vibe & Thrive allowance: Supporting your wellbeing, social connection, office setup, and more.

Flexible leave options: Empowering you to recharge and take time for what matters most.

Other stuff to know

We value unique experiences and skills. If you don’t meet every requirement but feel passionate about this role, we’d still love to hear from you.

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills, and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and its culture. Let us know your pronouns and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

Let’s make an impact together!
